Name: Arsene
FunFact: Arsene Lupin is a fictional gentleman thief created by Maurice Leblanc.

Name: Obariyon
FunFact: The Obariyon is a Japanese "piggyback demon" from local folklore.

Name: Orpheus(Female)
FunFact: Orpheus was so skilled at making music that he was called "Master of Strings" and "Father of Songs", capable of such music that even rocks and animals would be compelled to dance.

Name: Orpheus Picaro (Female)
FunFact: Orpheus was so skilled at making music that he was called "Master of Strings" and "Father of Songs", capable of such music that even rocks and animals would be compelled to dance.

Name: High Pixie
FunFact: They watch over the younger pixies as guardians, and ensure they are kept out of danger, although they are every bit as mischievous as their younger counterparts.

Name: Izanagi
FunFact: Izanagi is a Japanese creation deity born of the seven divine generations in Japanese mythology.

Name: Izanagi Picaro
FunFact: Izanagi is a Japanese creation deity born of the seven divine generations in Japanese mythology.

Name: Orpheus
FunFact: Compared to every other initial Personas in the Persona series, he has the worst affinities due to him having two weaknesses, without having any resistances to compensate

Name: Orpheus Picaro
FunFact: Compared to every other initial Personas in the Persona series, he has the worst affinities due to him having two weaknesses, without having any resistances to compensate

Name: Legion
FunFact: Legion is a single demon or a group of demons that combined into one which was referred in Christian literature.

Name: Ose
FunFact: He gives skill in all liberal sciences and true answers concerning divine and secret things. He can change any men into any shape the exorcist may desire, and the one that is changed will not know it.

Name: Bugs
FunFact: Bugbear was used to frighten children into behaving or obeying their parents.

Name: Crystal Skull*
FunFact: The Crystal Skulls were once believed to be pre-Columbian Mesoamerican artifacts. When all 13 skulls are closely gathered it is said to reveal the mysteries of the universe

Name: Black Frost
FunFact: Black Frost is Atlus' evil rendition of the more good-spirited demon Jack Frost.

Name: Raoul
FunFact: Despite being a third tier Persona, Raoul is a lower level than Satanael and has a weakness, when Satanael doesn't.

Name: Vishnu
FunFact: He is called The Preserver and is known for a kindly demeanor and genuine interest in the welfare of humanity.

Name: Satanael
FunFact: Satanael, also known as Sataniel, is mentioned as a leader of the fallen angels that rebelled against YHVH, by refusing to bow to the human Enoch, leading to his imprisonment. Due to his name and role, he is considered an interpretation of Lucifer.

Name: Zorro*
FunFact: He is a masked outlaw who defends commoners and the indigenous people of the land against tyrannical officials and other villains.

Name: Mercurius*
FunFact: Mercurius, also known as Mercury, is the Roman god of commerce, speed and merchants along with being the messenger god of the Dii Consentes, the roman pantheon of gods.

Name: Diego*
FunFact: The true name of Zorro.

Name: Pyro Jack
FunFact: In Japan, Pyro Jack is named after the fabled figure Jack-O'-Lantern.

Name: Cait Sith
FunFact: The Cait Sith appears in Irish and Scottish legends and served as the model for Puss-in-Boots.

Name: Jack Frost
FunFact: He is the official mascot of Atlus Co., Ltd.. Because of this, he makes recurring appearances in a number of Atlus games (primarily in the Megami Tensei series).

Name: Nekomata
FunFact: In Revelations: Persona, Nekomata was renamed Felicia as a reference to the character of the same name from Capcom's Darkstalkers fighting series.

Name: Sandman
FunFact: Originating from Northern European lore, the Sandman brings good dreams by sprinkling magical sand onto the eyes of children while they sleep at night.

Name: Choronzon
FunFact: Choronzon is mentioned by occultists in the 16th century, but became famous due to Aleister Crowley and his belief system, Thelema, described further in his book Liber AL vel Legis or the Book of Law.

Name: Queen Mab
FunFact: Queen Mab is said to be the queen of the Unseelie Court and the dark counterpart of the fairy queen Titania. She was first referred as a fairy in William Shakespeare's play Romeo and Juliet, where "she is the fairies' midwife."

Name: Rangda
FunFact: Rangda is the demon queen of the leyaks in Bali, according to traditional Balinese mythology. Terrifying to behold, the child-eating Rangda leads an army of evil witches against the leader of the forces of good, Barong.

Name: Forneus
FunFact: He is a Great Marquis of Hell with twenty-nine legions under his command, partly comprised of the order of angels and thrones, and appears as a sea monster.

Name: Surt
FunFact: It is also said to be the creator and the destroyer, as the fires of his realm created the stars of the heavens, and later during Ragnarok, it will rain down fire unto all land.

Name: Futsunushi
FunFact: Futsunushi-no-kami is a Shinto deity of swords. He is regarded as the personification of the sword Futsu-no-mitama.

Name: Johanna*
FunFact: Johanna's motorcycle design may be a reference to Pope Joan taking on a role primarily dominated by men, as pioneering motorcycles was primarily used by men until the early 1900s.

Name: Anat*
FunFact: Anat, also known as Anath, is a Semitic warrior goddess of war and sacrifice along with being the Syrian goddess that is associated with love, fertility and sex.

Name: Agnes*
FunFact: While references to a female pope go back to the 12th century, modern historians consider Pope Joan to be a fictional creation meant to discredit the church.

Name: Silky
FunFact: The Silky is a female fairy from the borders of Scotland, known to "wear rustling silk as she does household chores" and "terrorizes lazy servants."

Name: Apsaras
FunFact: Apsaras also known as Vidhya Dhari, according to Hindu and Buddhist mythology, are spirits that appear in the form of young, beautiful women who have mastered the fine art of celestial dance.

Name: Koh-i-Noor*
FunFact: The Koh-i-Noor is the world's largest natural colorless diamond mined from India.

Name: Isis
FunFact: She was worshiped as the ideal mother and wife, patron of nature and magic; friend of slaves, sinners, artisans and the downtrodden, as well as listening to the prayers of the wealthy, maidens, aristocrats and rulers.

Name: Kikuri-Hime
FunFact: Kikuri-Hime's second design which initially features in Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne serves as the base model for Uzume and Kushinada.

Name: Sarasvati
FunFact: Hindus believe that Sarasvati is the goddess of knowledge, music and the arts.

Name: Skadi
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne

Name: Scathach
FunFact: She is a legendary Scottish warrior woman and martial arts teacher who trains the legendary Ulster hero Cu Chulainn in the arts of combat.

Name: Cybele
FunFact: Cybele is also associated with various natural elements, including wildlife and vegetation.

Name: Milady*
FunFact: Milady's lack of a head may be a reference to Milady de Winter's death through beheading.

Name: Astarte*
FunFact: Astarte, also as Athtart or Ashtart, is a goddess worshiped under many names throughout the Mediterranean, she is a goddess associated with fertility, conflict, sex, love and war, along with being the deification of Venus.

Name: Lucy*
FunFact: Lucy is one of the few Personas in the series based on a historical figure, rather than a figure from mythology or folklore, that being Lucy Hay, Countess of Carlisle.

Name: Queens Necklace*
FunFact: Queen's Necklace originates from the infamous affair of the Diamond Necklace, which tarnished Queen Marie Antoinette's reputation, leading to the French Revolution and the queen's subsequent execution.

Name: Yaksini
FunFact: In the original Shin Megami Tensei, Yaksini is simply a recolored version of Kali.

Name: Lamia
FunFact: First Appeared in Megami Tensei

Name: Hariti
FunFact: A demoness originating from what is now called Pakistan, Hariti was originally an ogress who slew human children in her desperation to feed her hundreds of children.

Name: Dakini
FunFact: A dakini is a tantric deity described as an embodiment of enlightened energy that resembles a female.

Name: Titania
FunFact: Titania is derived from the fairy queen character in William Shakespeare's play "A Midsummer Night's Dream," which in traditional folklore had no name.

Name: Kali
FunFact: Kali is a Hindu goddess associated with death, time and destruction.

Name: Alilat
FunFact: Its origins are traced from the traditions of Sumerian civilization brought to pre-Islamic Arabia by merchants and nomads who idolized stones in their daily life.

Name: Mother Harlot
FunFact: Within the Book of Revelation, Mother Harlot is known as "Babylon the Great, Mother of Prostitutes and Abominations of the Earth," "Whore of Babylon", or The Harlot for short.

Name: Goemon*
FunFact: Goemon's weakness to Fire could be a reference to his execution in the pot of boiling oil.

Name: Kamu Susano-o*
FunFact: In Persona 5, Yusuke is implied to bring bad weather wherever he goes, which foreshadows his ultimate Persona as Kamu Susano-o.

Name: Gorokichi*
FunFact: The historical Gorokichi is only mentioned in two sources, both of which were created after his death.

Name: Regent*
FunFact: Regent is based on the Regent Diamond, a 141 carat diamond originating from India.

Name: Eligor
FunFact: He is a great duke and appears in the form of a goodly knight carrying a lance, pennon (flag) and a scepter. He can discover hidden objects, kindles love and lust, along with procuring the favor of lords and knights.

Name: Setanta
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne

Name: Thoth
FunFact: Thoth, also known Djehuti, is one of the most important gods in Egyptian mythology, commonly depicted as a man with the head of an ibis or baboon.

Name: Barong
FunFact: Starting from Shin Megami Tensei, the fusion of Barong and Rangda creates Shiva, one of the major gods of Hinduism who represents eternity, creation and destruction.

Name: King Frost
FunFact: King Frost's model in Persona 5/Royal contains numerous miniature Jack Frost models in it.

Name: Oberon
FunFact: He first became widely known when he appeared as a character in Shakespeare's " Midsummer Night's Dream,"but appeared earlier in the 13th century French epic "Huon of Bordeaux."

Name: Baal
FunFact: While it can actually refer to a large number of different deities, Baal in this case refers to Hadad, the Canaan god of rain, fertility, agriculture and thunder who is also one of the King of the Gods in the Canaanite pantheon.

Name: Odin
FunFact: Odin is often associated with lightning in the franchise, but in mythology he is never mentioned as a god of lightning or the sky, unlike his son Thor.

Name: Berith
FunFact: In the Sega CD version of Shin Megami Tensei, Berith is holding a sword opposed to the lance that he usually carries.

Name: Orobas
FunFact: Orobas is the 55th demonic spirit and a powerful great prince of Hell who could give conjurers perfect information about the past, present or future, bestow honors, reconcile them with foes and protect them from being tempted by demons.

Name: Anzu
FunFact: Anzu, mainly known as Zu, was a demonic tempest bird in Mesopotamian mythology, known for stealing the Tablet of Destinies from Enlil, the lord of the wind.

Name: Daisoujou
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei

Name: Mishaguji
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei

Name: Bishamonten
FunFact: He is depicted as the strongest of the Four Heavenly Kings, usually under the service of Taira no Masakado.

Name: Kohryu
FunFact: t is the embodiment of the element of Earth in Chinese five elements (Wu Xing).

Name: Carmen*
FunFact: Carmen is a fictive female gypsy created by Prosper Merimee. She first appeared in Merimee's eponymous novella that was first written and published in 1845.

Name: Hecate*
FunFact: She has been associated with childbirth, nurturing the young, gates and walls, doorways, crossroads, magic, lunar lore, torches and dogs.

Name: Celestine*
FunFact: Celestine Galli-Marie was a French mezzo-soprano who was most famous for her role of Carmen.

Name: Pixie
FunFact: According to artist Kazuma Kaneko, Pixie's character design, specifically her red wavy hair and leotard outfit, are inspired by Cham Huau from the anime Aura Battler Dunbine.

Name: Saki Mitama
FunFact: In Japanese belief, Saki Mitama is a part of the soul that brings good fortune and blessings.

Name: Ame no Uzume
FunFact: Ame no Uzume is the goddess of dawn and revelry in the Shinto religion of Japan. She famously relates to the tale of the missing sun deity, Amaterasu.

Name: Leanan Sidhe
FunFact: The Leanan Sidhe is generally depicted as a beautiful muse, who offers inspiration to an artist in exchange for fame and glory; however, this exchange frequently results in madness for the artist, and often premature death.

Name: Kushinada-Hime
FunFact: Kushinada-Hime's design for Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne is a reference to her transformation into a comb.

Name: Narcissus
FunFact: First Appeared in Devil Summoner: Soul Hackers

Name: Parvati
FunFact: Parvati is the Hindu goddess of fertility, love, beauty, harmony, marriage, children, and devotion; as well as of divine strength and power.

Name: Raphael
FunFact: His name means "It is God that heals." He is said to be the guardian of the Tree of Life.

Name: Ishtar
FunFact: Ishtar is the Babylonian goddess of love and fertility, the Babylonian equivalent of the Sumerian goddess Inanna.

Name: Captain Kidd*
FunFact: In an early concept of Captain Kidd, he appeared somewhat restrained in what appears to be a gibbet cage, which is a reference to William Kidd's body being gibbeted for three years after being hanged for piracy.

Name: Seiten Taisei*
FunFact: The incarnation of this Persona has a bludgeoning staff with a "8000K" written on it, a reference to the figure being able to lift anything at around 8,000 kilograms.

Name: William*
FunFact: William was the first third-tier Persona of the Phantom Thieves to be revealed.

Name: Agathion
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei: Devil Summoner

Name: Slime
FunFact: The appearance of Slimes in the Shin Megami Tensei series are stated to be the result of incomplete, faulty summons of demons. Mara resembles a Slime in its botched summoning form.

Name: Shiki-Ouji
FunFact: It could be used to scare away demons that cause sickness and to ward off disasters to its master.

Name: Kin-Ki
FunFact: Named after gold, Kin-Ki's body is so strong that no physical weapons in existence can pierce it.

Name: Ara Mitama
FunFact: Ara Mitama represents aggression and forcefulness and is the source of valor, anger, passion and other heated emotions.

Name: White Rider
FunFact: The White Rider is the first of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse to appear before John the Apostle, according to Christian scripture.

Name: Athena
FunFact: Athena is the Greek goddess of wisdom, courage, inspiration, civilization, philosophy, justice, law, mathematics, strength, arts, crafts, skill and reason.

Name: Athena Picaro
FunFact: Athena is the Greek goddess of wisdom, courage, inspiration, civilization, philosophy, justice, law, mathematics, strength, arts, crafts, skill and reason.

Name: Cerberus
FunFact: Cerberus is one of the earliest demon allies to appear as part of the Megami Tensei franchise. His roots put him as far back as the very first Digital Devil Story: Megami Tensei publications.

Name: Thor
FunFact: Despite being explicitly described as being red-haired, he is never depicted as such in games of the series.

Name: Chi You
FunFact: He is worshiped in China as the god of war and weapons and, along with Huang Di, as one of the progenitors of the Chinese people.

Name: Robin Hood*
FunFact: According to the comment in the Design Works, Robin Hood's design is based on the comic hero Superman.

Name: Loki*
FunFact: The sword wielded by Loki in Persona 5 is actually a pair of large pliers gripping a blade that is extremely hot, too hot to be touched.

Name: Hereward*
FunFact: Hereward's design may have been inspired by Batman, hence the black armor and the bat wing-like protrusions on the back of his head.

Name: Angel
FunFact: The are said to be manifestations of God's will and to rule and protect creation from all beings that seek to destroy it.

Name: Archangel
FunFact: Archangels are one of the few bodies of angels that contact those on the material plane directly and are the ministers and messengers between God and mankind.

Name: Principality
FunFact: As beings related to the world of the germinal ideas, they are said to inspire living things to many things such as art or science.

Name: Power
FunFact: It is said that they were the first order to be created. The Powers are the bearers of conscience and the keepers of history.

Name: Melchizedek
FunFact: Melchizedek, also known as Melchisedech, Melkisetek or Malki Tzedek, is a biblical figure known for his wisdom.

Name: Dominion
FunFact: In the Christian hierarchy of Angels, Dominions, also known as Lordships, are part of the second sphere and are said to watch over nations and regulate the duties of lesser angels.

Name: Throne
FunFact: Thrones are the third of nine classes of angels in Christianity, they are known as the angels of knowledge.

Name: Uriel
FunFact: He is said to carry the stars in the sky, and on the final day of judgement, he will oversee the resurrection and retribution of human souls.

Name: Metatron
FunFact: Whenever a human believes God has directly spoken to them, in reality it is Metatron acting as his vessel.

Name: Necronomicon*
FunFact: In the context of Lovecraft's works, the Necronomicon is a tome detailing the truth behind the various ancient cosmic beings that have inhabited Earth and continue to influence humans for their own ends.

Name: Prometheus*
FunFact: Prometheus was one of the Titans to sided with Zeus and his siblings in the great war against the rest of the Titans, the original rulers of the world.

Name: Al Azif*
FunFact: Al Azif is the original Arabic name for the Necronomicon.

Name: Bicorn
FunFact: Bicorn supposedly represents the sin of adultery. It is said that the unicorn was born from a bicorn and once had two horns itself.

Name: Koropokkuru
FunFact: Koropokkuru are a race of small people in Ainu folklore.

Name: Ippon-Datara
FunFact: Ippon-Datara is a rarely seen creature, one is more likely to see his footprints on the mountains. Some believe he might be a blacksmith or the ghost of one.

Name: Sudama
FunFact: Sudama are mischievous one footed spirits that roam the mountains, dwelling in trees and rocks.

Name: Naga
FunFact: They are also said to be the followers of Koumokuten, one of the Four Heavenly Kings

Name: Kurama Tengu
FunFact: The Kurama-Tengu are not only said to be exceptional warriors, but also have the ability to fend off disease and bring good luck.

Name: Arahabaki
FunFact: Arahabaki's design is based on the goggle-eyed doguu (or shakouki doguu), a type of clay figurine made during the Jomon period of prehistoric Japan (roughly 14,000 to 400 BC).

Name: Kumbhanda
FunFact: They are known to suck the life out of humans and are servants of the southern member of the Four Heavenly Kings, Zouchouten.

Name: Koumokuten
FunFact: His name means "vast/all-seeing eyes."

Name: Loa
FunFact: In Haitian mythology, Loa is an intermediary spirit between god and humans that expects to be properly served, not just communicated with.

Name: Fafnir
FunFact: Prior to Devil Summoner: Soul Hackers, Fafnir's design was a palette swap of Pendragon.

Name: Ongyo-ki
FunFact: Ongyo-ki suppressed its aura to prevent enemies from sensing him, allowing him to surprise enemies when he attacked. It has been allegedly said that this is the origin of ninjitsu.

Name: Stone of Scone*
FunFact: The Stone of Scone was used in the coronation of the monarchs of Scotland, and later was put to the same use by the monarchs of England and the United Kingdom.

Name: Clotho
FunFact: Clotho was responsible for spinning the thread of human life. She also made major decisions, such as when a person was born, thus in effect controlling people's lives.

Name: Ariadne
FunFact: First Appeared in Persona 4 Arena

Name: Lachesis
FunFact: She was the apportioner, deciding how much time for life was to be allowed for each person or being. She measured the thread of life with her rod.

Name: Atropos
FunFact: She is the one who cuts the thread of fate, signifying the end of one's life.

Name: Ariadne Picaro
FunFact: Ariadne was the daughter of King Minos of Crete, the owner of the Minotaur.

Name: Fortuna
FunFact: She can be represented veiled or blind. She used to be a goddess of blessing and fertility, mainly being worshiped by mothers.

Name: Norn
FunFact: Norn refers to the numerous female beings who rule the fates of the various races that exist.

Name: Asterius
FunFact: First Appeared in Persona 4 Arena

Name: Asterius Picaro
FunFact: First Appeared in Persona 4 Arena

Name: Lakshmi
FunFact: In Hindu mythos, Lakshmi is the goddess of beauty, good fortune and love and is the wife of Vishnu, one of the Trimurti.

Name: Kelpie
FunFact: In Celtic mythology, a kelpie is said to be a supernatural water horse that haunts rivers and lakes in Scotland and Ireland.

Name: Shiisaa
FunFact: A shishi-like creature said to be a protective spirit in Okinawan mythology.

Name: Oni
FunFact: They are popular characters in Japanese art, literature and theater. Oni are known for attacking villages and plundering food, riches and women.

Name: Rakshasa
FunFact: A rakshasa is a demon or unrighteous spirit in Hindu and Buddhist mythology.

Name: Orlov*
FunFact: It sets in the scepter named after the Russian Count, Grigory Grigorievich Orlov, by Empress Catherine the Great.

Name: Zouchouten
FunFact: His name means "lengthening good deeds among mortals."

Name: Valkyrie
FunFact: The valkyries bring their chosen to the afterlife hall of the slain, Valhalla, ruled over by the god Odin, where the deceased warriors become einherjar.

Name: Hanuman
FunFact: He is most famously known for aiding Rama (one of the avatars of Vishnu) in defeating the demon king Ravana by leading an army of monkeys.

Name: Chimera
FunFact: Chimera is the offspring of Typhon and Echidna, the mother of beasts, and is the sibling of Cerberus and Orthrus.

Name: Zaou-Gongen
FunFact: Zaou-Gongen, also known as Vajragarbha, is one of the most important mountain deities of Japan's syncretic Shugendou sects.

Name: Hua Po
FunFact: Hua Po is a kind of tree spirit said to be formed from the disembodied souls of dead humans when three or more people hang themselves from the same tree.

Name: Inugami
FunFact: Even so, while Inugami can betray their masters, they may also be the loyalest of companions.

Name: Orthrus
FunFact: Among his siblings were Cerberus, Sphinx and Chimera to name but a few.

Name: Take-Minakata
FunFact: He is the favorite demon of Kazuma Kaneko as evidenced in a Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne interview.

Name: Emperors Amulet*
FunFact: It once belonged to the King of the Franks Charles I.

Name: Hecatoncheir
FunFact: Having one hundred hands and fifty heads, their father Uranus found them disgusting and threw them into Tartarus.

Name: Jatayu
FunFact: First Appeared in Megami Tensei

Name: Moloch
FunFact: He was a demonic fertility deity, turned false deity, mentioned in varied theological writings; the most famous of which would be the Christian Bible.

Name: Macabre
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei: Strange Journey

Name: Attis
FunFact: Attis originated in the kingdom of Phrygia and eventually became a part of Greek lore.

Name: Mandrake
FunFact: In legend, if pulled from the ground, it makes a sound like scream of a dying child which is so horrible it either deafens or kills the person pulling it.

Name: Mokoi
FunFact: In Australian folklore, Mokoi are spirits of evil who kill those who used dark magic. They would also kidnap and eat children at night.

Name: Matador
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei II

Name: Nue
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei

Name: Pisaca
FunFact: Pisacas are demonic creatures that feast on human meat, especially corpses.

Name: Hell Biker
FunFact: Hell Biker's name in Japanese versions refers to Hells Angels, an American biker gang formed in 1948.

Name: Hope Diamond*
FunFact: The Hope Diamond is a grayish-blue diamond said to bring curses to the owner.

Name: Pale Rider
FunFact: The Pale Rider is the fourth and final Horseman of the Apocalypse, according to Christian scripture. The rider traditionally represents death.

Name: Chernobog
FunFact: He is also synonymous with evil and later became synonymous with the devil.

Name: Thanatos
FunFact: Thanatos is the personification and god of death and mortality in Greek mythology. He is commonly known as a harbinger of peaceful death.

Name: Thanatos Picaro
FunFact: The depiction of Thanatos in Persona 3 seems to be derived more from the earliest mythological accounts, being characterized as a grim warrior surrounded by a mantle of metal coffins.

Name: Mot
FunFact: Mot, also known as Mavet, is the Canaanite and Semitic god of death, infertility, drought and the Underworld.

Name: Alice
FunFact: Alice is said to be based on Lewis Carroll's  character from his famous story Alice in Wonderland, part of Through the Looking Glass.

Name: Genbu
FunFact: The Black Tortoise, also known as the Black Warrior, Black Tortoise of the North or simply Xuan Wu, is one of the four symbols of the Chinese constellation

Name: Koppa Tengu
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne

Name: Makami
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne

Name: Jikokuten
FunFact: Jikokuten, is a guardian deity with fierce expression that protects the east of Buddha's realm.

Name: Mithra
FunFact: In Zoroastrian mythology, Mithra was a deity of contracts who was the protector of truth and the enemy of error.

Name: Byakko
FunFact: The White Tiger, also known as the White Tiger of the West or Bai Hu, is one of the Four Symbols of the Chinese Constellation(Si Xiang)

Name: Raja Naga
FunFact: Raja Naga also appear in Buddhist mythology, and their duties consist of leading the nagas and protecting and worshipping the Buddha, along with protecting other enlightened beings.

Name: Gabriel
FunFact: Gabriel is a high-ranking messenger angel. Their name means "God is my strength" and is known to be the left hand of God and the embodiment of the holy spirit, in contrast to Michael who is the right hand of God.

Name: Ardha
FunFact: The god is male on one side and female on the other, depicted with the male half bearing aspects of Shiva and the female half bearing aspects of Parvati.

Name: Incubus
FunFact: An incubus is a demon in male form supposed to lie upon sleeping women in order to have sexual intercourse with them.

Name: Flauros
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei

Name: Andras
FunFact: According to the writings in The Lesser Key of Solomon, Andras is the sixty-third spirit listed in the Goetia. He is a Great Marquis of Hell with thirty legions of demons under his command.

Name: Lilim
FunFact: In Jewish folklore, Lilim (or Lilin) were dangerous creatures from Hell. They were said to be the children of Lilith by herself or by Samael, the angel of death.

Name: Pazuzu
FunFact: Pazuzu is the Mesopotamian god of the southwest wind known for bringing famine during dry seasons, and locusts during rainy seasons.

Name: Baphomet
FunFact: Baphomet is a King of Demons, known as the "Sabbatic Goat." He is identified with Satanachia, a senior demon general described in the Grand Grimoire.

Name: Nebiros
FunFact: He is supposedly the most valiant Marquis of Hell, has nineteen legions of demons under his command.

Name: Belial
FunFact: Belial, also known as Berial, is the 68th spirit in the Ars Goetia and one of the four crowned princes of Hell ruling over the North.

Name: Beelzebub
FunFact: The lord of the flies, Beelzebub was originally a Canaanite deity named Baal and was later explained to be one of the seven princes of Hell in Christian sources.

Name: Belphegor
FunFact: Belphegor gives people ideas for inventions that will make them rich and thus greedy and selfish.

Name: Red Rider
FunFact: The second of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse, named War. He represents war, and his horse is colored "fiery" red.

Name: Magatsu-Izanagi*
FunFact: Magatsu-Izanagi also represents "Emptiness."

Name: Magatsu-Izanagi Picaro*
FunFact: Magatsu-Izanagi is colored red; this alludes to the Magatsuhi in Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne, the substance consumed by demons visualized as red flowing spots.

Name: Seth
FunFact: Set is the deity of deserts, storms and chaos and served as one of the greatest deities in Egyptian myth.

Name: Black Rider
FunFact: The third of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse, riding a black horse, is popularly called Famine. The black color of the third horse symbolized death and famine.

Name: Mara
FunFact: In Buddhist myth, Mara is a tempter, through the deceit of regarding the mundane and negative as alluring, and personifies unwholesome impulses, unskillfulness and the "death" of the spiritual life.

Name: Yoshitsune
FunFact: Yoshitsune is one of the few demons in the series based on a historical figure, rather than a figure from mythology or folklore.

Name: Mada
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne

Name: Kodama
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne

Name: Neko Shogun
FunFact: Neko Shogun is a divine general in the image of a cat.

Name: Kaiwan
FunFact: Kaiwan, also known as Rephan, is an Astro-Mythological star deity in Assyrian mythology and that was worshiped by the Israelites before God was accepted.

Name: Garuda
FunFact: The Garuda is a large mythical bird or bird-like creature that appears in both Hindu and Buddhist mythology.

Name: Vasuki
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei: Devil Summoner

Name: Sraosha
FunFact: Sraosha is known as the "ear" of Ahura Mazda, and one of the oldest and most ethical of the Yazatas, being the greatest one of them in Zoroastrianism.

Name: Hastur
FunFact: While Hastur is best known as part of the Cthulhu Mythos, he was originally created by Ambrose Bierce in the short story "Haita The Shepherd."

Name: Lucifer
FunFact: Lucifer is the demon who represents the sin of Pride.

Name: Succubus
FunFact: A Succubus is a demon from European folklore during the medieval ages, which takes the form of an attractive female to seduce men.

Name: Onmoraki
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei IMAGINE

Name: Kaguya
FunFact: Kaguya Hime is a character from a very famous Japanese folk story called Taketori Monogatari

Name: Black Ooze
FunFact: First Appeared in Shin Megami Tensei

Name: Sui-Ki
FunFact: One of the four oni controlled by Fujiwara-no-Chikata. Named after water, Sui-ki can freeze anything to the core.

Name: Kaguya Picaro
FunFact: Parts of Kaguya's face and robes resemble Kusumi-no-Okami's.

Name: Mothman
FunFact: Mothman is a cryptid of American origin. In the mid-1960s, there were some sightings of a great winged creature with massive reddish eyes.

Name: Girimehkala
FunFact: It is suggested that Girimekhala is a demonized Ganesha or Airavata from Hinduism, as Buddhist Sri Lankans and the Hindu Indians have come into conflict several times throughout history.

Name: Tsukuyomi
FunFact: The lunar god in Shintoism. He was born of Izanagi's right eye as he bathed after his descent to the underworld, thus making him the brother of Amaterasu and Susano-O.

Name: Tsukiyomi Picaro
FunFact: The lunar god in Shintoism. He was born of Izanagi's right eye as he bathed after his descent to the underworld, thus making him the brother of Amaterasu and Susano-O.

Name: Lilith
FunFact: Lilith was originally a storm demon known as "Lilitu" in ancient Mesopotamian myth around 3000 BC and she was thought to have been the cause of disease, illness, and death.

Name: Byakhee
FunFact: First Appeared in Persona 2: Eternal Punishment

Name: Sandalphon
FunFact: Sandalphon is an archangel or seraphim that is prominently featured in Jewish mysticism, such as the Kabbalah where he resides in the Sephirot of Malkuth alongside his "twin brother" Metatron.

Name: Suzaku
FunFact: The Zhu Que, also known as Vermilion Bird of the South or simply the Vermilion Bird, is one of theFour Symbols of the Chinese constellations(Si Xiang).

Name: Thunderbird
FunFact: The Thunderbird is a legendary creature found in Native American folklore. It's considered a "supernatural" bird of power and strength.

Name: Mithras
FunFact: Mithras is a sun deity who was worshiped in the Roman empire from the 1st to the 4th century AD and is the patron of Mithraism.

Name: Yurlungur
FunFact: In aboriginal Australian mythology, the Yurlungur is a great copper snake that is said to bring the rains and thus incite the renewal of life.

Name: Horus
FunFact: First Appeared in Megami Tensei II

Name: Ganesha
FunFact: Ganesha is one of the most worshiped deities in the Hindu pantheon and is known as the Lord of Obstacles, Lord of Beginnings, god of wisdom and intelligence and patron of arts and science

Name: Quetzalcoatl
FunFact: First Appeared in Megami Tensei I

Name: Asura
FunFact: Asuras are entities that take on varying roles in the Asian religions.

Name: Anubis
FunFact: Anubis is widely known as the Egyptian deity of mummification.

Name: Trumpeter
FunFact: The Trumpeter is based on one of the angels mentioned in the Book of Revelation of the New Testament.

Name: Yamata no Orochi
FunFact: Yamata no Orochi is an eight-headed and eight-tailed serpent from Japanese lore.

Name: Abaddon
FunFact: In the later teachings of Revelation, Abaddon had become a being that personified the abyss, becoming known as the "Angel of the Abyss."

Name: Messiah
FunFact: A messiah is regarded as the savior of mankind and would bring them salvation near to the end of days, although opinions between who the messiah refers to differs between religions.

Name: Shiva
FunFact: In the Hindu religion, Shiva the Destroyer is one of the three principal deities of the Trimurti (Hindu Triad) along with Brahma the Creator and  Vishnu the Preserver.

Name: Michael
FunFact: Michael, also known as Mikail in Islam, is an Archangel, one of the principal 50 angels in Christian lore, and of the four archangels of Islamic tradition.

Name: Messiah Picaro
FunFact: A messiah is regarded as the savior of mankind and would bring them salvation near to the end of days, although opinions between who the messiah refers to differs between religions.

Name: Satan
FunFact: The skill Black Viper is a reference to the snake that tempted Adam and Eve to eat the forbidden fruit.

Name: Cendrillon*
FunFact: Cendrillon is the French adaptation of the classic folk tale Cinderella.

Name: Freya*
FunFact: Freya is portrayed as a goddess of love, beauty and fertility. Blonde, blue-eyed and beautiful, Freya is described as the fairest of all goddesses, and people prayed to her for happiness in love.

Name: Ella*
FunFact: Cinderella is not the actual name of the character (which, in some adaptions, is Ella), but a nickname from her stepfamily as she was often covered in cinders when sleeping next to a fireplace to keep warm.

Name: Feng Huang
FunFact: Suzaku was mistakenly translated as Feng Huang in the English localization of many games in the Shin Megami Tensei franchise, including

Name: Tam Lin
FunFact: Tam Lin is a famous fairy who was said to haunt Caterhaugh Wood in England. He supposedly lured young women away to ruin them.

Name: Unicorn
FunFact: Unicorns are said to have originated from Bicorns, and once had two horns. They are also thought to have been invented later as symbols of good to oppose the "evil" bicorns.

Name: Okuninushi
FunFact: Okuninushi's image was described as the "Japanese version of Cu Chulainn" during the production of Shin Megami Tensei III: Nocturne.

Name: Orichalcum*
FunFact: Orichalcum is a yellow metal, prized in ancient times, and mentioned in stories like Atlantis.

Name: Atavaka
FunFact: Unused Persona data for Atavaka can be found in Persona 5. It would later be officially added in Persona 5 Royal.

Name: Cu Chulainn
FunFact: In 2017, Chu Chulainn was voted as the third most popular Demon in the Megami Tensei series.

Name: Siegfried
FunFact: Siegfried is the dragon-slaying hero of the medieval German epic Das Nibelungenlied, most widely known due to its adaptation by Richard Wagner into a series of four operas,Der Ring des Nibelungen.

Name: Maria
FunFact: Maria's latest design very likely takes inspiration from the cathedral of Sagrada Familia in Barcelona, Spain. This choice was likely influenced by the fact that the architect was a fervent devotee of the virgin Mary.

Name: Azathoth*
FunFact: Azathoth, also known as The Blind Idiot God, the Nuclear Chaos, the Daemon Sultan, The Deep Dark, The Cold One, Achamoth or Vach-Viraj, is an Outer God in Lovecraft's Cthulhu Mythos.

Name: Adam Kadmon*
FunFact: Adam Kadmon is the original man in the teachings of Kabbalah, untainted by earthly matter. He stands in contrast to the Adam of Eden, who was made from earthly clay.

Name: Kusi Mitama
FunFact: It is believed to be have mysterious powers, to cause transformations and to be able to cure illnesses, as according to Shinto belief.

Name: Nigi Mitama
FunFact: In Japanese belief, it is the calm and functional state of a person's soul, or kami.

Name: Decarabia
FunFact: In 2017, Decarabia was voted as the seventh most popular Demon in the Megami Tensei series.

Name: Ananta
FunFact: According to Hindu mythology, Ananta is the King of all Nagas.

Name: Yatagarasu
FunFact: In Japanese mythology, Yatagarasu has the appearance of the great bird and represents the will of heaven or divine intervention in human affairs.

Name: Seiryu
FunFact: In some official English versions this demon is incorrectly translated as Long

Name: Dionysus

FunFact: In Zoroastrian mythology, he is one of the six Amesha Spentas.

Name: Izanagi-no-Okami
